-- usage --

parses time strings into milliseconds:

```js
import ms from '@prsm/ms'

ms('1h 30m')        // 5400000
ms('10s')           // 10000
ms('-30min')        // -1800000
ms(100)             // 100 (numbers pass through)
```

-- options --

second arg can be a default value (for invalid inputs) or an options object:

```js
ms('invalid', '5m')              // 300000 (default)
ms('10.9ms', { round: false })   // 10.9
ms('1000ms', { unit: 's' })      // 1
```

-- used by --

@prsm/queue uses this for delay and timeout options ("100ms", "5s", "1m").
@eaccess/auth uses this for session durations, remember token expiry, etc.
